c: 18
v: 22
t: "They will say: \"[They were] three, the fourth of them being their dog;\" while [others] will say: \"Five, the sixth of them is their dog,\" guessing at the Unseen. [Still others] say: \"Seven, and the eighth of them is their dog.\" SAY: \"My Lord is quite Aware as to how many they were. Only a few know about them.\" Do not discuss them except in a discussion that is obvious, nor seek anyone else´s opinion about them"